{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878955304,"sessionID":"ses_28560f931ffe4C5vIqrKBCG3xA","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa25cc1001KCIMplrc4OM8dY","messageID":"msg_d7aa2485d001r1PgvI7qspPGg2","sessionID":"ses_28560f931ffe4C5vIqrKBCG3xA","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ed56f5b6f6f24d41888de297","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n2: \n3: **Module:** .github\n4: **Language:** YAML\n5: **Size:** L\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: 为 AgentCube 项目建立完整的 GitHub Actions CI/CD 流水线体系，覆盖 PR 门禁验证、镜像发布、端到端测试、代码质量检查和贡献者工作流审批。当前项目已通过 AR-033 建立了 Makefile 构建入口，但尚未有自动化 CI/CD 来保证代码合入质量、自动发布多架构容器镜像、运行 Kind E2E 测试集群、检查 Python SDK 质量以及管理首次贡献者的工作流审批。本变更将 12 个独立 workflow 收敛至 `.github/workflows/` 目录，利用 `dorny/paths-filter` 实现按需触发，减少不必要的 CI 资源消耗，确保每次 PR 合入都经过构建、测试、lint、代码生成校验、拼写和版权一致性检查。\n10: \n11: ## Scope\n12: \n13: ### In Scope\n14: \n15: - **12 个 GitHub Actions workflow 文件创建：**\n16:   1. **`main.yml`** — Agentcube CI Workflow：PR 到 `main`/`release-*` 时构建 Workload Manager Docker 镜像（`make docker-build`）\n17:   2. **`lint.yml`** — Go Lint：Go 文件变更时运行 `make lint`（golangci-lint），路径过滤 `**/*.go`、`go.mod`、`go.sum`、`.golangci.yml`\n18:   3. **`test-coverage.yml`** — Test Coverage：PR/merge_group 时运行 race-enabled 覆盖率测试（`go test -race -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`），支持 Codecov 上传\n19:   4. **`e2e.yml`** — E2E Tests：PR 到 `main`/`release-*` 时运行 `make e2e`，使用 Kind v0.30.0（`install_only: true`），失败时上传 e2e 日志，始终执行 `make e2e-clean`\n20:   5. **`codegen-check.yml`** — Codegen Check：API/hack/workflow/Makefile 变更时运行 `make gen-check`（`gen-all` + `git diff --exit-code`），Go 1.24.4\n21:   6. **`copyright-check.yml`** — Copyright Check：非文档/图片文件变更时运行 `make gen-copyright` + `git diff --exit-code`，安装 `moreutils`（`sponge`）\n22:   7. **`codespell.yml`** — Codespell：PR 到 `main`/`release-*` 时运行拼写检查，临时移开 `pyproject.toml`、`package.json`、`package-lock.json` 避免误报\n23:   8. **`python-sdk-tests.yml`** — Python SDK Tests：`sdk-python/**` 变更时运行 pytest（Python 3.12，editable install）\n24:   9. **`python-lint.yml`** — Python Lint：Python 路径变更时运行 Ruff（Python 3.10，`ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`）\n25:   10. **`build-push-release.yml`** — Build and Push Release Images：push 到 `main` 或语义化版本 tag 时构建并推送多架构镜像（workloadmanager、router、picod）到 GHCR\n26:   11. **`dify-plugin-publish.yml`** — Dify Plugin Publish：`dify-plugin/v*` tag 时打包 Dify 插件并自动向 `langgenius/dify-plugins` 仓库提交 PR\n27:   12. **`workflows-approve.yml`** — Approve Workflows：`pull_request_target` labeled/synchronize 事件时，自动审批非首次贡献者或带 `ok-to-test` 标签的 pending workflow runs\n28: \n29: - **路径过滤策略：** 使用 `dorny/paths-filter@v3` 实现精确的变更路径检测，避免无关 workflow 运行\n30: - **Go 版本矩阵：** Go 1.24（lint/coverage/codegen）、Go 1.24.4（codegen-check/release）、Go 1.23（e2e）\n31: - **Python 版本：** 3.12（SDK 测试）、3.10（Python lint）\n32: - **Kind 版本：** v0.30.0（E2E 集群）\n33: - **镜像发布：** 支持 `main` 分支推送（`latest` tag）和 `v*.*.*`/`v*.*.*-*` 语义化版本 tag 推送\n34: - **Secret 管理：** `CODECOV_TOKEN`（可选，通过 `workflow_call` 声明）、`GITHUB_TOKEN`（registry login、cross-repo PR）、`PLUGIN_ACTION`（Dify 插件发布）\n35: \n36: ### Out of Scope\n37: \n38: - Makefile 目标的变更（由 AR-033 处理，本 AR 仅消费现有目标）\n39: - Dockerfile 内容的变更（由 AR-032 处理）\n40: - Docusaurus 文档站点的 CI/CD（由后续文档 AR 处理）\n41: - Volcano scheduler 镜像构建和发布（非 AgentCube 核心组件）\n42: - 对现有 Go 源码、Python SDK、Helm chart 的任何功能性修改\n43: - 第三方 CI 平台集成（如 Jenkins、GitLab CI、CircleCI）\n44: \n45: ## Architecture Summary\n46: \n47: **当前状态（Before）：**\n48: \n49: 项目无任何 `.github/workflows/` 目录或 CI/CD 配置。开发者提交 PR 后：\n50: \n51: 1. 无自动构建验证 — 无法确认 Docker 镜像能否成功构建\n52: 2. 无自动测试 — Go 单元测试、Python SDK 测试、E2E 测试均需手动运行\n53: 3. 无代码质量门禁 — golangci-lint、Ruff、codespell、版权检查均未自动化\n54: 4. 无自动发布流程 — 多架构镜像推送需手动执行 `make docker-buildx-push*`\n55: 5. 无贡献者工作流审批 — 首次贡献者的 workflow runs 需手动 approve\n56: 6. 无代码生成漂移检测 — `make gen-all` 生成的文件可能与源码不同步\n57: \n58: 问题：\n59: 1. 低质量代码可能合入 main 分支\n60: 2. 发布流程依赖人工操作，容易遗漏步骤\n61: 3. 无 E2E 验证，集成问题只能在部署后发现\n62: 4. 拼写错误和缺失版权头需人工 review 发现\n63: \n64: **目标状态（After）：**\n65: \n66: ```\n67: PR opened to main/release-*\n68:   │\n69:   ├── main.yml ──────────────── docker build (make docker-build)\n70:   ├── lint.yml ──────────────── go lint (make lint) [if *.go changed]\n71:   ├── test-coverage.yml ─────── go test -race -cover [if pkg/ changed]\n72:   ├── e2e.yml ───────────────── make e2e on Kind cluster\n73:   ├── codegen-check.yml ─────── make gen-check [if API/hack changed]\n74:   ├── copyright-check.yml ───── make gen-copyright + git diff\n75:   ├── codespell.yml ─────────── codespell scan\n76:   ├── python-sdk-tests.yml ──── pytest [if sdk-python/ changed]\n77:   └── python-lint.yml ───────── ruff check [if python changed]\n78: \n79: Push to main or tag v*.*.*\n80:   └── build-push-release.yml ── multi-arch build + push to ghcr.io\n81: \n82: Tag dify-plugin/v*\n83:   └── dify-plugin-publish.yml ── package + PR to langgenius/dify-plugins\n84: \n85: PR labeled/synchronize\n86:   └── workflows-approve.yml ──── auto-approve for repeat contributors\n87: ```\n88: \n89: **Workflow 触发矩阵：**\n90: \n91: | Workflow | PR to main | PR to release-* | merge_group | push main | push tag | labeled/sync |\n92: |----------|:----------:|:---------------:|:-----------:|:---------:|:--------:|:------------:|\n93: | main.yml | ✅ | ✅ | | | | |\n94: | lint.yml | ✅ | ✅ | | | | |\n95: | test-coverage.yml | ✅ | | ✅ | | | |\n96: | e2e.yml | ✅ | ✅ | | | | |\n97: | codegen-check.yml | ✅ | ✅ | | | | |\n98: | copyright-check.yml | ✅ | ✅ | | | | |\n99: | codespell.yml | ✅ | ✅ | | | | |\n100: | python-sdk-tests.yml | ✅ | | ✅ | | | |\n101: | python-lint.yml | ✅ | ✅ | | | | |\n102: | build-push-release.yml | | | | ✅ | ✅ | |\n103: | dify-plugin-publish.yml | | | | | ✅ (dify-plugin/v*) | |\n104: | workflows-approve.yml | ✅ (target) | ✅ (target) | | | | ✅ |\n105: \n106: **路径过滤配置：**\n107: \n108: | Workflow | Filter name | Paths |\n109: |----------|-------------|-------|\n110: | lint.yml | `lint` | `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` |\n111: | test-coverage.yml | `coverage` | `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` |\n112: | codegen-check.yml | `codegen` | `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` |\n113: | copyright-check.yml | `copyright` | all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` |\n114: | python-sdk-tests.yml | `sdk` | `sdk-python/**` |\n115: | python-lint.yml | `python` | `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml` |\n116: \n117: ## Impact Analysis\n118: \n119: | Area | Impact |\n120: |------|--------|\n121: | **Consumers** | 所有贡献者受益：PR 自动验证 9 项检查，合入信心显著提升；维护者减少手动 review 负担；首次贡献者通过 `workflows-approve.yml` 获得自动化审批体验 |\n122: | **Backward compatibility** | 无破坏性变更 — 新增 `.github/workflows/` 目录，不修改任何现有源码、Dockerfile、Helm chart 或 Makefile；仅消费 AR-033 定义的 Makefile 目标 |\n123: | **Dependencies** | 引入 GitHub Actions 官方 action（checkout、setup-go、setup-python、docker/build-push-action 等）和社区 action（dorny/paths-filter@v3、helm/kind-action@v1、codecov/codecov-action、peter-evans/create-pull-request）；所有 action 均通过 hash 或版本 pin 锁定 |\n124: | **Security** | `GITHUB_TOKEN` 权限最小化（仅 registry login 和 cross-repo PR 所需）；`CODECOV_TOKEN` 为可选 secret；`build-push-release.yml` 仅响应 `main` 分支和语义化 tag 推送，防止任意分支触发镜像发布；`dorny/paths-filter` 在 PR 场景使用 `pull_request` 事件（非 `pull_request_target`），避免恶意 PR 读取 secret |\n125: | **Performance** | 路径过滤减少不必要的 workflow 运行（如纯文档 PR 不触发 Go lint/测试）；`test-coverage.yml` 使用 `free-disk-space` 步骤确保大仓库有足够空间跑覆盖率；E2E workflow 使用 `install_only: true` 避免 Kind 集群重复创建 |\n126: | **Operations** | CI 失败时自动上传日志 artifact（E2E 日志、覆盖率报告）；`workflows-approve.yml` 自动化减少维护者手动 approve 操作；发布流程完全自动化，tag 推送即触发多架构镜像构建和 GHCR 推送 |\n127: \n128: ## Alternatives Considered\n129: \n130: | Alternative | Pros | Cons | Decision |\n131: |-------------|------|------|----------|\n132: | **保持现状，无 CI/CD** | 零维护成本，无 action 依赖 | 低质量代码可能合入；发布依赖人工操作；无 E2E 验证；贡献者体验差 | Rejected — 不可接受，项目已达到需要自动化验证的复杂度 |\n133: | **单个 monolithic workflow（所有检查在一个 .yml 中）** | 文件少，易于管理 | 运行时间长（所有检查串行或并行但共享 runner）；无法按路径过滤跳过无关检查；失败定位困难；难以独立重试单个检查 | Rejected — 12 个独立 workflow 提供更好的模块化、按需触发和故障隔离 |\n134: | **使用 CircleCI / GitLab CI / Jenkins** | 更灵活的 runner 配置；支持自托管 runner | 需要额外基础设施维护；GitHub 原生集成度低（PR 状态、secret 管理、action 生态）；AgentCube 已在 GitHub 托管，引入外部 CI 增加复杂度 | Rejected — GitHub Actions 与仓库同平台，零额外基础设施，action 生态成熟 |\n135: | **使用 reusable workflows（`workflow_call`）抽象公共逻辑** | 减少重复配置；集中管理 Go/Python 版本 | 增加复杂度（需要维护被调用的 workflow 文件）；当前 12 个 workflow 的差异较大（触发条件、路径过滤、命令不同），抽象收益有限 | Partially adopted — `test-coverage.yml` 声明了 `workflow_call` 接口以便未来复用，但其他 workflow 保持独立 |\n136: | **本方案（12 个独立 workflow + paths-filter）** | 按需触发减少 CI 资源消耗；每个 workflow 职责单一；失败定位清晰；与 Makefile 目标解耦（Makefile 变更不影响 workflow 逻辑）；行业标准实践 | 文件数量较多（12 个 .yml）；需要维护 paths-filter 配置与项目路径的一致性 | **Accepted** — 在模块化、可维护性和 CI 效率之间取得最佳平衡 |\n137: \n138: ## Upstream Dependencies\n139: \n140: - **AR-033（Makefile 构建目标体系）** — 本 AR 的 workflow 消费 AR-033 定义的 Makefile 目标（`make docker-build`、`make lint`、`make gen-check`、`make gen-copyright`、`make e2e`、`make e2e-clean`、`make docker-buildx-push*`）\n141: - **AR-032（Dockerfile 多阶段构建）** — `main.yml` 和 `build-push-release.yml` 依赖 Dockerfile 存在且可构建\n142: - 无其他 AR 依赖 — 本变更为独立的 CI/CD 基础设施\n143: \n144: ## Status\n145: \n146: - [ ] Proposal review\n147: - [ ] Implementation\n148: - [ ] Verification\n\n(End of file - total 148 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n\n**Module:** .github\n**Language:** YAML\n**Size:** L\n\n## Purpose\n\n为 AgentCube 项目建立完整的 GitHub Actions CI/CD 流水线体系，覆盖 PR 门禁验证、镜像发布、端到端测试、代码质量检查和贡献者工作流审批。当前项目已通过 AR-033 建立了 Makefile 构建入口，但尚未有自动化 CI/CD 来保证代码合入质量、自动发布多架构容器镜像、运行 Kind E2E 测试集群、检查 Python SDK 质量以及管理首次贡献者的工作流审批。本变更将 12 个独立 workflow 收敛至 `.github/workflows/` 目录，利用 `dorny/paths-filter` 实现按需触发，减少不必要的 CI 资源消耗，确保每次 PR 合入都经过构建、测试、lint、代码生成校验、拼写和版权一致性检查。\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n- **12 个 GitHub Actions workflow 文件创建：**\n  1. **`main.yml`** — Agentcube CI Workflow：PR 到 `main`/`release-*` 时构建 Workload Manager Docker 镜像（`make docker-build`）\n  2. **`lint.yml`** — Go Lint：Go 文件变更时运行 `make lint`（golangci-lint），路径过滤 `**/*.go`、`go.mod`、`go.sum`、`.golangci.yml`\n  3. **`test-coverage.yml`** — Test Coverage：PR/merge_group 时运行 race-enabled 覆盖率测试（`go test -race -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`），支持 Codecov 上传\n  4. **`e2e.yml`** — E2E Tests：PR 到 `main`/`release-*` 时运行 `make e2e`，使用 Kind v0.30.0（`install_only: true`），失败时上传 e2e 日志，始终执行 `make e2e-clean`\n  5. **`codegen-check.yml`** — Codegen Check：API/hack/workflow/Makefile 变更时运行 `make gen-check`（`gen-all` + `git diff --exit-code`），Go 1.24.4","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775878955296,"end":1775878955302}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878956558,"sessionID":"ses_28560f931ffe4C5vIqrKBCG3xA","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa261a0001XEYqiVm7zPk472","messageID":"msg_d7aa2485d001r1PgvI7qspPGg2","sessionID":"ses_28560f931ffe4C5vIqrKBCG3xA","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3eebdbbf898247ad97b6cd70","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `.github`\n6: - **Language:** YAML\n7: - **Size:** L\n8: - **Base specs:** (No directly matching specs)\n9: \n10: ## Scope\n11: \n12: This delta spec covers the creation of 12 GitHub Actions workflow files under `.github/workflows/` that provide a complete CI/CD pipeline for the AgentCube project. The workflows SHALL cover PR build verification, Go linting, test coverage, E2E testing on Kind, code generation drift checks, copyright/spelling checks, Python SDK tests and linting, multi-architecture release image publication, Dify plugin publishing, and automated workflow approval for repeat contributors. All workflows SHALL use `dorny/paths-filter@v3` for path-based conditional execution where applicable, and SHALL consume Makefile targets defined in AR-033 without modifying any existing source code, Dockerfiles, or Helm charts.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Workflow 1: main.yml — Agentcube CI Workflow\n17: \n18: ### Requirement: Docker build on PR to main/release-*\n19: \n20: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/main.yml` that builds the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n21: \n22: #### Scenario: PR to main triggers docker build\n23: - **GIVEN** a pull request targeting the `main` branch\n24: - **WHEN** the `Agentcube CI Workflow` job runs\n25: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: PR to release-* triggers docker build\n28: - **GIVEN** a pull request targeting a `release-*` branch\n29: - **WHEN** the workflow is triggered\n30: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make docker-build` with the same steps as for `main`\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: PR to feature branch does NOT trigger workflow\n33: - **GIVEN** a pull request targeting a `feature/*` branch\n34: - **WHEN** the PR is opened\n35: - **THEN** the `main.yml` workflow SHALL NOT be triggered\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: Docker build failure fails the check\n38: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile contains a syntax error\n39: - **WHEN** `make docker-build` executes in the workflow\n40: - **THEN** the workflow job SHALL fail with a non-zero exit code\n41: \n42: ---\n43: \n44: ## Workflow 2: lint.yml — Go Lint\n45: \n46: ### Requirement: Path-filtered Go lint on PR\n47: \n48: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/lint.yml` that runs `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Go file changes trigger lint\n51: - **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter `lint` matches `**/*.go`\n52: - **WHEN** the Lint workflow runs\n53: - **THEN** it SHALL use Go `1.24` and execute `make lint`\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: go.mod changes trigger lint\n56: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies `go.mod` or `go.sum`\n57: - **WHEN** the path filter `lint` is evaluated\n58: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Lint workflow SHALL run\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: .golangci.yml changes trigger lint\n61: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies `.golangci.yml`\n62: - **WHEN** the path filter `lint` is evaluated\n63: - **THEN** it SHALL match (`.golangci.yml` is in the filter paths) and the Lint workflow SHALL run\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Workflow file changes trigger lint\n66: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n67: - **WHEN** the path filter `lint` is evaluated\n68: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Lint workflow SHALL run\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: No Go changes skip lint\n71: - **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies `docs/README.md`\n72: - **WHEN** the path filter `lint` is evaluated\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT match and the Lint workflow SHALL skip the lint job\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Lint failure fails the check\n76: - **GIVEN** Go source code contains a golangci-lint violation\n77: - **WHEN** `make lint` executes\n78: - **THEN** the workflow job SHALL fail with a non-zero exit code\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## Workflow 3: test-coverage.yml — Test Coverage\n83: \n84: ### Requirement: Race-enabled coverage tests on PR/merge_group\n85: \n86: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` that runs race-enabled coverage tests on `pkg/...` for qualifying pull requests and merge groups, with optional Codecov upload.\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Coverage test on PR\n89: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` and path filter `coverage` matches\n90: - **WHEN** the Test Coverage job runs with Go `1.24`\n91: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Coverage test on merge_group\n94: - **GIVEN** a `merge_group` event and path filter `coverage` matches\n95: - **WHEN** the Test Coverage job runs\n96: - **THEN** it SHALL execute the same coverage command as for PR\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: Coverage artifact upload\n99: - **GIVEN** the coverage test completes successfully\n100: - **WHEN** the post-test step runs\n101: - **THEN** `coverage.out` SHALL be uploaded as a workflow artifact\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: Optional Codecov upload\n104: - **GIVEN** the `CODECOV_TOKEN` secret is configured and passed via `workflow_call`\n105: - **WHEN** the coverage job completes\n106: - **THEN** it SHALL upload the coverage report to Codecov via `codecov/codecov-action`\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Codecov upload skipped when token absent\n109: - **GIVEN** the `CODECOV_TOKEN` secret is not configured\n110: - **WHEN** the coverage job completes\n111: - **THEN** the Codecov upload step SHALL be skipped without failing the workflow\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Coverage path filter excludes docs/media\n114: - **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies `*.md`, `*.svg`, or `*.png` files\n115: - **WHEN** the path filter `coverage` is evaluated\n116: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT match and the coverage job SHALL be skipped\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Free disk space step\n119: - **GIVEN** the runner has limited disk space\n120: - **WHEN** the coverage job starts\n121: - **THEN** it SHALL run a `free-disk-space` step to ensure sufficient space for coverage data\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ## Workflow 4: e2e.yml — E2E Tests\n126: \n127: ### Requirement: E2E testing on Kind cluster\n128: \n129: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` that runs `make e2e` in CI using a Kind-capable Ubuntu runner, capturing logs on failure.\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: E2E job on PR to main\n132: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n133: - **WHEN** the E2E workflow runs\n134: - **THEN** it SHALL set `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`\n135: \n136: #### Scenario: Kind installation\n137: - **GIVEN** the E2E workflow is running\n138: - **WHEN** the Kind setup step executes\n139: - **THEN** it SHALL install Kind tool `v0.30.0` with `install_only: true`\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: E2E test execution\n142: - **GIVEN** the Kind cluster is ready\n143: - **WHEN** the E2E step runs\n144: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make e2e` with Go `1.23`\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: E2E failure uploads logs\n147: - **GIVEN** `make e2e` fails\n148: - **WHEN** the workflow reaches the post-test step\n149: - **THEN** it SHALL upload the `e2e-logs` directory as a workflow artifact\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: E2E cleanup always runs\n152: - **GIVEN** the E2E workflow completes (pass or fail)\n153: - **WHEN** the cleanup step executes\n154: - **THEN** it SHALL always run `make e2e-clean`\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: E2E uses ubuntu runner\n157: - **GIVEN** the E2E workflow is triggered\n158: - **WHEN** the job runner is selected\n159: - **THEN** it SHALL use an Ubuntu runner with Kind capability\n160: \n161: ---\n162: \n163: ## Workflow 5: codegen-check.yml — Codegen Check\n164: \n165: ### Requirement: Code generation drift detection\n166: \n167: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` that verifies generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change.\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: API changes trigger codegen check\n170: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `pkg/apis/**`\n171: - **WHEN** the path filter `codegen` is evaluated\n172: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Codegen Check workflow SHALL run\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Hack directory changes trigger codegen check\n175: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `hack/**`\n176: - **WHEN** the path filter `codegen` is evaluated\n177: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Codegen Check workflow SHALL run\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Workflow changes trigger codegen check\n180: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `.github/workflows/**`\n181: - **WHEN** the path filter `codegen` is evaluated\n182: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Codegen Check workflow SHALL run\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: Makefile changes trigger codegen check\n185: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies the `Makefile`\n186: - **WHEN** the path filter `codegen` is evaluated\n187: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Codegen Check workflow SHALL run\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: Codegen check uses Go 1.24.4\n190: - **GIVEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs\n191: - **WHEN** Go is set up\n192: - **THEN** it SHALL use version `1.24.4`\n193: \n194: #### Scenario: Gen-check runs gen-all and diff\n195: - **GIVEN** the codegen check job is executing\n196: - **WHEN** the check step runs\n197: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make gen-check` (which runs `gen-all` followed by `git diff --exit-code`)\n198: \n199: #### Scenario: Generated code drift fails the check\n200: - **GIVEN** generated files are out of sync with source (e.g., CRD changed but not regenerated)\n201: - **WHEN** `make gen-check` executes\n202: - **THEN** `git diff --exit-code` SHALL detect the difference and the workflow SHALL fail\n203: \n204: ---\n205: \n206: ## Workflow 6: copyright-check.yml — Copyright Check\n207: \n208: ### Requirement: Copyright header verification\n209: \n210: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` that ensures `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n211: \n212: #### Scenario: Source file changes trigger copyright check\n213: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies a Go source file\n214: - **WHEN** the path filter `copyright` is evaluated\n215: - **THEN** it SHALL match (Go files are not in the exclusion list) and the Copyright Check workflow SHALL run\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: Markdown changes skip copyright check\n218: - **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies `*.md` files\n219: - **WHEN** the path filter `copyright` is evaluated\n220: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT match (`*.md` is excluded) and the workflow SHALL skip\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: SVG/PNG changes skip copyright check\n223: - **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies `*.svg` or `*.png` files\n224: - **WHEN** the path filter `copyright` is evaluated\n225: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT match and the workflow SHALL skip\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: Docs directory changes skip copyright check\n228: - **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies files under `docs/**`\n229: - **WHEN** the path filter `copyright` is evaluated\n230: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT match and the workflow SHALL skip\n231: \n232: #### Scenario: .github directory changes skip copyright check\n233: - **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies files under `.github/**`\n234: - **WHEN** the path filter `copyright` is evaluated\n235: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT match and the workflow SHALL skip\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: Copyright check installs moreutils\n238: - **GIVEN** the copyright check job is running\n239: - **WHEN** the setup step executes\n240: - **THEN** it SHALL install `moreutils` (providing `sponge`) via `apt-get`\n241: \n242: #### Scenario: Copyright gen produces no diff\n243: - **GIVEN** all source files have correct copyright headers\n244: - **WHEN** `make gen-copyright` runs followed by `git diff --exit-code`\n245: - **THEN** the diff SHALL be empty and the workflow SHALL pass\n246: \n247: #### Scenario: Missing copyright header fails the check\n248: - **GIVEN** a new source file lacks the required copyright header\n249: - **WHEN** `make gen-copyright` runs followed by `git diff --exit-code`\n250: - **THEN** the diff SHALL detect the added header and the workflow SHALL fail\n251: \n252: ---\n253: \n254: ## Workflow 7: codespell.yml — Codespell\n255: \n256: ### Requirement: Spelling check on PR\n257: \n258: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` that runs codespell on the repository for pull requests to `main` or `release-*`, temporarily moving files that cause false positives.\n259: \n260: #### Scenario: Codespell runs on PR to main\n261: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n262: - **WHEN** the Codespell workflow runs\n263: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository and install codespell via `pip install codespell`\n264: \n265: #### Scenario: False-positive files are temporarily moved\n266: - **GIVEN** the codespell job is about to run\n267: - **WHEN** the pre-check step executes\n268: - **THEN** it SHALL back up and remove `pyproject.toml`, `package-lock.json`, `package.json` from the repo root (and nested copies per `find`)\n269: \n270: #### Scenario: Codespell invocation with skip patterns\n271: - **GIVEN** false-positive files have been moved\n272: - **WHEN** codespell runs\n273: - **THEN** it SHALL use `--check-filenames`, specified `--skip` globs, and `--ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn` on the `.` directory\n274: \n275: #### Scenario: Files are restored after codespell\n276: - **GIVEN** codespell has completed (pass or fail)\n277: - **WHEN** the post-check step executes\n278: - **THEN** it SHALL restore all backed-up files to their original locations\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: Spelling error fails the check\n281: - **GIVEN** a source file contains a misspelled word not in the ignore list\n282: - **WHEN** codespell runs\n283: - **THEN** it SHALL report the error and the workflow SHALL fail\n284: \n285: ---\n286: \n287: ## Workflow 8: python-sdk-tests.yml — Python SDK Tests\n288: \n289: ### Requirement: Python SDK unit tests on path change\n290: \n291: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` that runs pytest for the SDK when `sdk-python/**` changes.\n292: \n293: #### Scenario: SDK file changes trigger tests\n294: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `sdk-python/**`\n295: - **WHEN** the path filter `sdk` is evaluated\n296: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Python SDK Tests workflow SHALL run\n297: \n298: #### Scenario: Python 3.12 is used\n299: - **GIVEN** the Python SDK Tests job is running\n300: - **WHEN** Python is set up\n301: - **THEN** it SHALL use version `3.12`\n302: \n303: #### Scenario: Editable install\n304: - **GIVEN** the Python SDK Tests job is in the `sdk-python/` working directory\n305: - **WHEN** the setup step executes\n306: - **THEN** it SHALL run `pip install -e .`\n307: \n308: #### Scenario: Pytest execution\n309: - **GIVEN** the SDK is installed in editable mode\n310: - **WHEN** the test step runs\n311: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n312: \n313: #### Scenario: SDK test failure fails the check\n314: - **GIVEN** a Python SDK test is failing\n315: - **WHEN** `python -m pytest tests/ -v` executes\n316: - **THEN** the workflow job SHALL fail with a non-zero exit code\n317: \n318: #### Scenario: No SDK changes skip tests\n319: - **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies Go source files\n320: - **WHEN** the path filter `sdk` is evaluated\n321: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT match and the Python SDK Tests workflow SHALL skip\n322: \n323: ---\n324: \n325: ## Workflow 9: python-lint.yml — Python Lint\n326: \n327: ### Requirement: Python lint with Ruff\n328: \n329: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` that runs Ruff from repository root using `pyproject.toml` when Python-touching paths change.\n330: \n331: #### Scenario: CLI code changes trigger Python lint\n332: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `cmd/cli/**`\n333: - **WHEN** the path filter `python` is evaluated\n334: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Python Lint workflow SHALL run\n335: \n336: #### Scenario: SDK changes trigger Python lint\n337: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `sdk-python/**`\n338: - **WHEN** the path filter `python` is evaluated\n339: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Python Lint workflow SHALL run\n340: \n341: #### Scenario: Example code changes trigger Python lint\n342: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `example/**`\n343: - **WHEN** the path filter `python` is evaluated\n344: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Python Lint workflow SHALL run\n345: \n346: #### Scenario: Test Python files trigger lint\n347: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files matching `test/**/*.py`\n348: - **WHEN** the path filter `python` is evaluated\n349: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Python Lint workflow SHALL run\n350: \n351: #### Scenario: pyproject.toml changes trigger lint\n352: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies `pyproject.toml`\n353: - **WHEN** the path filter `python` is evaluated\n354: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Python Lint workflow SHALL run\n355: \n356: #### Scenario: Python lint uses Python 3.10\n357: - **GIVEN** the Python Lint job is running\n358: - **WHEN** Python is set up\n359: - **THEN** it SHALL use version `3.10`\n360: \n361: #### Scenario: Ruff check execution\n362: - **GIVEN** Python is set up and ruff is installed\n363: - **WHEN** the lint step runs\n364: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n365: \n366: #### Scenario: Ruff violation fails the check\n367: - **GIVEN** a Python file contains a Ruff-detectable issue\n368: - **WHEN** `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` executes\n369: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL fail with a non-zero exit code\n370: \n371: ---\n372: \n373: ## Workflow 10: build-push-release.yml — Build and Push Release Images\n374: \n375: ### Requirement: Multi-architecture release image publication\n376: \n377: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` that builds and pushes multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and on semantic version tags.\n378: \n379: #### Scenario: Push to main builds latest images\n380: - **GIVEN** a push event to the `main` branch\n381: - **WHEN** the workflow is triggered\n382: - **THEN** `TAG` SHALL be set to `latest` and multi-arch images SHALL be built and pushed\n383: \n384: #### Scenario: Semantic version tag builds tagged images\n385: - **GIVEN** a push event with `github.ref_type` equal to `tag` matching `v*.*.*` or `v*.*.*-*`\n386: - **WHEN** the workflow is triggered\n387: - **THEN** `TAG` SHALL be set to `github.ref_name` (e.g., `v0.1.0`) and images SHALL be tagged accordingly\n388: \n389: #### Scenario: GHCR login\n390: - **GIVEN** the release build job is running\n391: - **WHEN** the registry login step executes\n392: - **THEN** it SHALL log in to `ghcr.io` using `GITHUB_TOKEN`\n393: \n394: #### Scenario: Image registry is set correctly\n395: - **GIVEN** the release build job is running\n396: - **WHEN** the build steps execute\n397: - **THEN** `IMAGE_REGISTRY` SHALL be set to `ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}`\n398: \n399: #### Scenario: Workloadmanager image is built and pushed\n400: - **GIVEN** the release workflow is running\n401: - **WHEN** the workloadmanager build step executes\n402: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make docker-buildx-push-workloadmanager` with the correct `IMAGE_REGISTRY` and `WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE`\n403: \n404: #### Scenario: Router image is built and pushed\n405: - **GIVEN** the release workflow is running\n406: - **WHEN** the router build step executes\n407: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make docker-buildx-push-router` with the correct `IMAGE_REGISTRY` and `ROUTER_IMAGE`\n408: \n409: #### Scenario: Picod image is built and pushed\n410: - **GIVEN** the release workflow is running\n411: - **WHEN** the picod build step executes\n412: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make docker-buildx-push-picod` with the correct `IMAGE_REGISTRY` and `PICOD_IMAGE`\n413: \n414: #### Scenario: Non-matching tag does NOT trigger release\n415: - **GIVEN** a push event with a tag that does NOT match semantic versioning (e.g., `docs-update`)\n416: - **WHEN** the workflow trigger is evaluated\n417: - **THEN** the `build-push-release.yml` workflow SHALL NOT be triggered\n418: \n419: #### Scenario: Feature branch push does NOT trigger release\n420: - **GIVEN** a push to a `feature/*` branch\n421: - **WHEN** the workflow trigger is evaluated\n422: - **THEN** the `build-push-release.yml` workflow SHALL NOT be triggered\n423: \n424: ---\n425: \n426: ## Workflow 11: dify-plugin-publish.yml — Dify Plugin Publish\n427: \n428: ### Requirement: Dify plugin packaging and PR submission\n429: \n430: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` that packages a Dify plugin and automatically submits a PR to the `langgenius/dify-plugins` repository when a `dify-plugin/v*` tag is pushed.\n431: \n432: #### Scenario: Dify plugin tag triggers publish\n433: - **GIVEN** a push event with tag matching `dify-plugin/v*`\n434: - **WHEN** the workflow is triggered\n435: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository and package the Dify plugin\n436: \n437: #### Scenario: Plugin packaging\n438: - **GIVEN** the dify-plugin-publish workflow is running\n439: - **WHEN** the packaging step executes\n440: - **THEN** it SHALL create a distributable plugin archive from the `dify-plugin/` directory\n441: \n442: #### Scenario: PR submission to langgenius/dify-plugins\n443: - **GIVEN** the plugin is packaged\n444: - **WHEN** the PR submission step executes\n445: - **THEN** it SHALL use `peter-evans/create-pull-request` to create a PR against `langgenius/dify-plugins`\n446: \n447: #### Scenario: PLUGIN_ACTION secret is used for authentication\n448: - **GIVEN** the PR submission step requires cross-repo access\n449: - **WHEN** the step executes\n450: - **THEN** it SHALL use the `PLUGIN_ACTION` secret for authentication\n451: \n452: #### Scenario: Non-dify-plugin tag does NOT trigger workflow\n453: - **GIVEN** a push event with tag `v0.1.0` (not matching `dify-plugin/v*`)\n454: - **WHEN** the workflow trigger is evaluated\n455: - **THEN** the `dify-plugin-publish.yml` workflow SHALL NOT be triggered\n456: \n457: ---\n458: \n459: ## Workflow 12: workflows-approve.yml — Approve Workflows\n460: \n461: ### Requirement: Automated workflow approval for repeat contributors\n462: \n463: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` that optionally approves pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n464: \n465: #### Scenario: pull_request_target on labeled event\n466: - **GIVEN** a `pull_request_target` event on `main` or `release-*` with `labeled` or `synchronize` type\n467: - **WHEN** the workflow is triggered\n468: - **THEN** it SHALL evaluate the contributor's PR history\n469: \n470: #### Scenario: Repeat contributor is auto-approved\n471: - **GIVEN** the PR author has more than one PR in the repository\n472: - **WHEN** the approval step executes\n473: - **THEN** it SHALL list workflow runs for the head SHA with `status: action_required` and call `approveWorkflowRun` for each\n474: \n475: #### Scenario: ok-to-test label triggers approval\n476: - **GIVEN** the PR has the `ok-to-test` label (regardless of contributor history)\n477: - **WHEN** the approval step executes\n478: - **THEN** it SHALL approve all pending workflow runs for the PR\n479: \n480: #### Scenario: First-time contributor without label is NOT approved\n481: - **GIVEN** the PR author has only one PR and the PR does NOT have the `ok-to-test` label\n482: - **WHEN** the approval step evaluates\n483: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT approve any workflow runs\n484: \n485: #### Scenario: No action_required runs to approve\n486: - **GIVEN** all workflow runs for the head SHA have already started or completed\n487: - **WHEN** the approval step lists runs with `status: action_required`\n488: - **THEN** the list SHALL be empty and the step SHALL succeed without action\n489: \n490: ---\n491: \n492: ## Workflow Trigger Matrix\n493: \n494: ### Requirement: Workflow trigger correctness\n495: \n496: Each workflow SHALL be triggered only by the events specified in the trigger matrix.\n497: \n498: #### Scenario: PR to main triggers 9 workflows\n499: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` with changes across all paths\n500: - **WHEN** the PR is opened\n501: - **THEN** the following workflows SHALL be triggered: `main.yml`, `lint.yml`, `test-coverage.yml`, `e2e.yml`, `codegen-check.yml`, `copyright-check.yml`, `codespell.yml`, `python-sdk-tests.yml`, `python-lint.yml`\n502: \n503: #### Scenario: Push to main triggers release workflow\n504: - **GIVEN** a push to `main`\n505: - **WHEN** the push event is processed\n506: - **THEN** only `build-push-release.yml` SHALL be triggered (with `TAG=latest`)\n507: \n508: #### Scenario: Semantic version tag triggers release workflow\n509: - **GIVEN** a push of tag `v0.2.0`\n510: - **WHEN** the push event is processed\n511: - **THEN** only `build-push-release.yml` SHALL be triggered (with `TAG=v0.2.0`)\n512: \n513: #### Scenario: Dify plugin tag triggers plugin publish\n514: - **GIVEN** a push of tag `dify-plugin/v1.0.0`\n515: - **WHEN** the push event is processed\n516: - **THEN** only `dify-plugin-publish.yml` SHALL be triggered\n517: \n518: #### Scenario: PR labeled ok-to-test triggers approval\n519: - **GIVEN** a PR to `main` receives the `ok-to-test` label\n520: - **WHEN** the `labeled` event fires\n521: - **THEN** `workflows-approve.yml` SHALL be triggered\n522: \n523: ---\n524: \n525: ## Path Filter Configuration\n526: \n527: ### Requirement: dorny/paths-filter usage\n528: \n529: All workflows that use conditional path-based execution SHALL use `dorny/paths-filter@v3` with correctly configured path patterns.\n530: \n531: #### Scenario: lint filter matches Go files\n532: - **GIVEN** the `lint.yml` workflow defines filter `lint`\n533: - **WHEN** the filter paths are inspected\n534: - **THEN** they SHALL include `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n535: \n536: #### Scenario: coverage filter excludes docs/media\n537: - **GIVEN** the `test-coverage.yml` workflow defines filter `coverage`\n538: - **WHEN** the filter paths are inspected\n539: - **THEN** they SHALL match `**` with negative patterns excluding `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`\n540: \n541: #### Scenario: codegen filter matches generation inputs\n542: - **GIVEN** the `codegen-check.yml` workflow defines filter `codegen`\n543: - **WHEN** the filter paths are inspected\n544: - **THEN** they SHALL include `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile`\n545: \n546: #### Scenario: copyright filter excludes non-code files\n547: - **GIVEN** the `copyright-check.yml` workflow defines filter `copyright`\n548: - **WHEN** the filter paths are inspected\n549: - **THEN** they SHALL match all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**`\n550: \n551: #### Scenario: sdk filter matches Python SDK\n552: - **GIVEN** the `python-sdk-tests.yml` workflow defines filter `sdk`\n553: - **WHEN** the filter paths are inspected\n554: - **THEN** they SHALL include `sdk-python/**`\n555: \n556: #### Scenario: python filter matches all Python paths\n557: - **GIVEN** the `python-lint.yml` workflow defines filter `python`\n558: - **WHEN** the filter paths are inspected\n559: - **THEN** they SHALL include `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`\n560: \n561: ---\n562: \n563: ## Security\n564: \n565: ### Requirement: Secret management and permission minimization\n566: \n567: Workflows SHALL use secrets and permissions following the principle of least privilege.\n568: \n569: #### Scenario: GITHUB_TOKEN used only for registry login\n570: - **GIVEN** the `build-push-release.yml` workflow runs\n571: - **WHEN** the GHCR login step executes\n572: - **THEN** it SHALL use `GITHUB_TOKEN` with only the permissions required for container registry write access\n573: \n574: #### Scenario: CODECOV_TOKEN is optional\n575: - **GIVEN** the `test-coverage.yml` workflow runs\n576: - **WHEN** the Codecov upload step is evaluated\n577: - **THEN** it SHALL check for the presence of `CODECOV_TOKEN` and skip gracefully if absent\n578: \n579: #### Scenario: PLUGIN_ACTION secret for cross-repo access\n580: - **GIVEN** the `dify-plugin-publish.yml` workflow runs\n581: - **WHEN** the PR creation step executes\n582: - **THEN** it SHALL use `PLUGIN_ACTION` secret for authentication to the external `langgenius/dify-plugins` repository\n583: \n584: #### Scenario: pull_request_target is NOT used for code execution\n585: - **GIVEN** the `workflows-approve.yml` workflow\n586: - **WHEN** the workflow is inspected\n587: - **THEN** it SHALL use `pull_request_target` ONLY for the approval action (which does not execute repository code), not for any step that checks out or runs repository code\n588: \n589: ---\n590: \n591: ## File Changes\n592: \n593: | Action | File | Description |\n594: |--------|------|-------------|\n595: | Create | `.github/workflows/main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow: Docker build on PR to main/release-* |\n596: | Create | `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | Go Lint: path-filtered golangci-lint on Go file changes |\n597: | Create | `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage: race-enabled coverage tests with optional Codecov upload |\n598: | Create | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` | E2E Tests: Kind-based E2E testing with log artifact upload on failure |\n599: | Create | `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check: detect drift between generated artifacts and source |\n600: | Create | `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check: verify copyright headers via make gen-copyright |\n601: | Create | `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` | Codespell: spelling check with false-positive file handling |\n602: | Create | `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests: pytest on sdk-python changes |\n603: | Create | `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` | Python Lint: Ruff check on Python path changes |\n604: | Create | `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release: multi-arch images to GHCR on main push or version tag |\n605: | Create | `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish: package plugin and PR to langgenius/dify-plugins |\n606: | Create | `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows: auto-approve pending runs for repeat contributors |\n\n(End of file - total 606 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `.github`\n- **Language:** YAML\n- **Size:** L\n- **Base specs:** (No directly matching specs)\n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec covers the creation of 12 GitHub Actions workflow files under `.github/workflows/` that provide a complete CI/CD pipeline for the AgentCube project. The workflows SHALL cover PR build verification, Go linting, test coverage, E2E testing on Kind, code generation drift checks, copyright/spelling checks, Python SDK tests and linting, multi-architecture release image publication, Dify plugin publishing, and automated workflow approval for repeat contributors. All workflows SHALL use `dorny/paths-filter@v3` for path-based conditional execution where applicable, and SHALL consume Makefile targets defined in AR-033 without modifying any existing source code, Dockerfiles, or Helm charts.\n\n---\n\n## Workflow 1: main.yml — Agentcube CI Workflow\n\n### Requirement: Docker build on PR to main/release-*\n\nThe system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/main.yml` that builds the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775878956545,"end":1775878956555}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878957678,"sessionID":"ses_28560f931ffe4C5vIqrKBCG3xA","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa2667f0015zWx41c3bPOL21","messageID":"msg_d7aa2485d001r1PgvI7qspPGg2","sessionID":"ses_28560f931ffe4C5vIqrKBCG3xA","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9077f745ca0b4774bb035419","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/ci-cd/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/ci-cd/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CI/CD — Design\n2: \n3: Sources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n4: \n5: ## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n6: \n7: | Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n8: |----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n9: | `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | — | — |\n10: | `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` → `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | — |\n11: | `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | — | — |\n12: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | — |\n13: | `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | — | — |\n14: | `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n15: | `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | — | — |\n16: | `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | — | — |\n17: | `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none — scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | — | — |\n18: | `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` → `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n19: | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n20: | `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` → `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | — | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |\n21: \n22: ### Workflow notes\n23: \n24: - **`e2e.yml`**: Uses Kind action with `install_only: true` so the cluster is created by `run_e2e.sh` (`kind create cluster`), avoiding double-creation.\n25: - **`test-coverage.yml`**: `workflow_call` declares `CODECOV_TOKEN` optional for reusable invocation; PR runs use the repo secret when configured.\n26: - **`build-push-release.yml`**: Uses older action major versions (`checkout@v3`, `setup-go@v4`, `buildx@v2`) than most other workflows.\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## E2E test setup (`test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n31: \n32: ### Kind cluster\n33: \n34: | Item | Value / behavior |\n35: |------|------------------|\n36: | Default cluster name | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` → `agentcube-e2e` |\n37: | Creation | `kind create cluster --name \"${E2E_CLUSTER_NAME}\"` if missing; if exists and `E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER=true` (default), delete then recreate |\n38: | CI alignment | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` installs Kind **v0.30.0** via `helm/kind-action@v1` (`install_only: true`) |\n39: | Skip setup | `E2E_SKIP_SETUP=true` skips `run_setup` and assumes an existing cluster |\n40: \n41: ### CRD / agent-sandbox installation\n42: \n43: Applied via `kubectl apply --validate=false` after downloading release assets (URLs built from `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`, default **`v0.1.1`**):\n44: \n45: 1. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/manifest.yaml`\n46: 2. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/extensions.yaml`\n47: \n48: ### Images pre-pulled and loaded into Kind\n49: \n50: - `registry.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/agent-sandbox-controller:${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}`\n51: - `python:3.9-slim` (echo agent workload)\n52: \n53: Local images built and loaded:\n54: \n55: - `make docker-build` → default `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` **`workloadmanager:latest`**\n56: - `make docker-build-router` → **`agentcube-router:latest`**\n57: - `make docker-build-picod` → **`picod:latest`**\n58: - `REDIS_IMAGE` default **`redis:7-alpine`** (Deployment + Service in namespace)\n59: \n60: ### Helm (AgentCube chart)\n61: \n62: | Item | Value |\n63: |------|--------|\n64: | Chart path | `manifests/charts/base` |\n65: | Release / namespace | `agentcube` in `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (default `agentcube`), `--create-namespace` |\n66: | Redis addr | `redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379`, password empty |\n67: | Workload manager image | `repository=workloadmanager`, `tag=latest` |\n68: | Router image | `repository=agentcube-router`, `tag=latest` |\n69: | Router RBAC | `router.rbac.create=true`, `router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router` |\n70: | Extra env (JSON via `--set-json`) | Workload manager: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`, `JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE=agentcube`; Router: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n71: | Wait | `helm upgrade --install ... --wait` |\n72: \n73: ### Kubernetes fixtures applied during setup\n74: \n75: | Path | Purpose |\n76: |------|---------|\n77: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | `AgentRuntime` `echo-agent` in `agentcube` |\n78: | Generated from `echo_agent.yaml` (sed) | `echo-agent-short-ttl` with `sessionTimeout: \"30s\"` for TTL tests |\n79: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` `e2e-code-interpreter` in `agentcube` |\n80: \n81: Warm-pool Go tests apply `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` at runtime (not in initial `kubectl apply` list in the shell script).\n82: \n83: ### Port forwards and health checks\n84: \n85: - Workload manager: `kubectl port-forward svc/workloadmanager` → `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8080**) → pod 8080\n86: - Router: `kubectl port-forward svc/agentcube-router` → `ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8081**) → pod 8080\n87: - Readiness: `curl` to `http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}/health` and `http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}/health/live`\n88: \n89: ### Auth for tests\n90: \n91: - ServiceAccount `e2e-test` in `agentcube` + `ClusterRoleBinding` to `workloadmanager` clusterrole\n92: - API token: `kubectl create token e2e-test -n agentcube --duration=24h` → `API_TOKEN`\n93: \n94: ### Python venv for E2E\n95: \n96: - Directory: `E2E_VENV_DIR` (default `/tmp/agentcube-e2e-venv`)\n97: - `python3 -m venv`, `pip install -e ./sdk-python`, verify `import agentcube`\n98: \n99: ### Test commands invoked by `run_e2e.sh`\n100: \n101: **Go** (from repository root):\n102: \n103: ```bash\n104: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n105: ROUTER_URL=\"http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n106: API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n107: go test -v ./test/e2e/...\n108: ```\n109: \n110: **Python** (after `cd` to `test/e2e`):\n111: \n112: ```bash\n113: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"...\" ROUTER_URL=\"...\" API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n114: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE=\"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n115: \"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py\n116: ```\n117: \n118: (`test_codeinterpreter.py` uses `unittest.main()` and appends `--verbose` if missing.)\n119: \n120: ### Failure artifacts\n121: \n122: On test failure, `collect_component_logs` writes under `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (CI: `${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`): workload manager, router, and sandbox pod logs/describes.\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## Test directory structure\n127: \n128: ```\n129: test/\n130: ├── OWNERS\n131: └── e2e/\n132:     ├── README.md\n133:     ├── __init__.py\n134:     ├── run_e2e.sh\n135:     ├── e2e_test.go\n136:     ├── test_codeinterpreter.py\n137:     ├── echo_agent.yaml\n138:     ├── e2e_code_interpreter.yaml\n139:     └── e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml\n140: ```\n141: \n142: ### Fixture paths (relative to repo root unless noted)\n143: \n144: | Fixture | Description |\n145: |---------|-------------|\n146: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | Echo `AgentRuntime` for router invocation tests |\n147: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | Standard `CodeInterpreter` (`e2e-code-interpreter`, namespace `agentcube`) |\n148: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` with `warmPoolSize: 2` in `default` (loaded by Go tests from **package cwd** as `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml`) |\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## Go test commands and flags in CI\n153: \n154: | Workflow / entrypoint | Command | Flags / notes |\n155: |------------------------|---------|----------------|\n156: | `test-coverage.yml` | `go test` | `-race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` |\n157: | `e2e.yml` via `make e2e` → `run_e2e.sh` | `go test` | `-v ./test/e2e/...` with env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `API_TOKEN` |\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## Python test commands in CI\n162: \n163: | Workflow | Working dir | Command |\n164: |----------|-------------|---------|\n165: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | `sdk-python` | `python -m pip install --upgrade pip`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` |\n166: | `e2e.yml` (via `run_e2e.sh`) | Invoked from `test/e2e/` | `\"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py` (unittest, verbosity 2) |\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## Key Make targets referenced by CI\n171: \n172: | Target | Referenced in | Role |\n173: |--------|----------------|------|\n174: | `docker-build` | `main.yml`, `run_e2e.sh` | Build workload manager image |\n175: | `docker-build-router` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build router image |\n176: | `docker-build-picod` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build picod image |\n177: | `docker-buildx-push` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push workload manager image (`IMAGE_REGISTRY`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE=workloadmanager:${TAG}`) |\n178: | `docker-buildx-push-router` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push router image |\n179: | `docker-buildx-push-picod` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push picod image |\n180: | `e2e` | `e2e.yml` | Run `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n181: | `e2e-clean` | `e2e.yml` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n182: | `lint` | `lint.yml` | `golangci-lint` (project default) |\n183: | `gen-check` | `codegen-check.yml` | Verify generated code up to date |\n184: | `gen-copyright` | `copyright-check.yml` | Generate copyright headers for check |\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## Additional reference: E2E README vs script\n189: \n190: `test/e2e/README.md` states Go **1.24+** and generic “install CRDs and agent-sandbox”; the **CI workflow** pins Go **1.23** for E2E, and **run_e2e.sh** pins **agent-sandbox `v0.1.1`** by default (overridable via `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`).\n\n(End of file - total 190 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CI/CD — Design\n\nSources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n\n## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n\n| Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n|----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n| `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | — | — |\n| `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` → `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | — |\n| `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | — | — |\n| `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | — |\n| `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | — | — |\n| `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n| `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | — | — |\n| `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | — | — |\n| `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none — scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | — | — |\n| `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` → `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n| `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n| `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` → `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | — | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/ci-cd/design.md","time":{"start":1775878957658,"end":1775878957676}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878959305,"sessionID":"ses_28560f931ffe4C5vIqrKBCG3xA","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa26ada001dEcXGgZ2P9Zfyt","messageID":"msg_d7aa2485d001r1PgvI7qspPGg2","sessionID":"ses_28560f931ffe4C5vIqrKBCG3xA","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_c870a9f7dcc344058500f26d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/ci-cd/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/ci-cd/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # CI/CD Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Automate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Pull request build verification\n9: The system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n12: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n13: - **WHEN** the “Agentcube CI Workflow” job runs\n14: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\n17: The system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n20: - **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n21: - **WHEN** the Lint workflow runs\n22: - **THEN** it SHALL use Go `1.24` and execute `make lint`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Code generation check\n25: The system SHALL verify generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Regenerate and diff\n28: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, or `Makefile`\n29: - **WHEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs with Go `1.24.4`\n30: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make gen-check` (which runs `gen-all` and `git diff --exit-code`)\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Go test coverage reporting\n33: The system SHALL run race-enabled coverage tests on `pkg/...` for qualifying pull requests and merge groups, optionally uploading to Codecov.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Coverage command\n36: - **GIVEN** path filter `coverage` matches (broad glob excluding some media/docs per workflow)\n37: - **WHEN** the Test Coverage job runs with Go `1.24`\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` and upload `coverage.out` as an artifact\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: E2E testing on Kind\n41: The system SHALL run `make e2e` in CI using a Kind-capable Ubuntu runner, capturing logs on failure.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: E2E job lifecycle\n44: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n45: - **WHEN** the E2E workflow runs\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL set `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`, install Kind tool `v0.30.0` (`install_only: true`), run `make e2e` with Go `1.23`, upload `e2e-logs` on failure, and always run `make e2e-clean`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Python SDK unit tests\n49: The system SHALL run pytest for the SDK when `sdk-python/**` changes.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Editable install and pytest\n52: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `sdk-python/**`\n53: - **WHEN** the Python SDK Tests job runs with Python `3.12` in `sdk-python/`\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install pytest`, `pip install -e .`, and run `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: Python lint\n57: The system SHALL run Ruff from repository root using `pyproject.toml` when Python-touching paths change.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Ruff check\n60: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, or the workflow file\n61: - **WHEN** the Python Lint job runs with Python `3.10`\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install ruff` and run `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: Spelling check (codespell)\n65: The system SHALL run codespell on the repository for pull requests to `main` or `release-*`, temporarily moving files that cause false positives.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Codespell invocation\n68: - **GIVEN** checkout complete\n69: - **WHEN** codespell runs after backup/remove of `pyproject.toml`, `package-lock.json`, `package.json` at repo root (and nested copies per `find`)\n70: - **THEN** it SHALL use `pip install codespell` and run codespell with `--check-filenames`, specified `--skip` globs, and `--ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn` on `.`, then restore backed-up files\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Copyright header check\n73: The system SHALL ensure `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Copyright workflow\n76: - **GIVEN** path filter marks `copyright` (all paths minus exclusions for md/svg/png/docs/.github per workflow)\n77: - **WHEN** the job runs\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL install `moreutils` (`sponge`), run `make gen-copyright`, and `git diff --exit-code`\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Release image publication\n81: The system SHALL build and push multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and on semantic version tags.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Tag selects image tag\n84: - **GIVEN** a `push` event\n85: - **WHEN** `github.ref_type` is `tag`, environment `TAG` SHALL be `github.ref_name`; otherwise `TAG` SHALL be `latest`\n86: - **THEN** the job SHALL log in to `ghcr.io` with `GITHUB_TOKEN` and run `make docker-buildx-push*`, setting `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` and per-image `*_IMAGE=<name>:${TAG}`\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Workflow approval for first-time contributors\n89: The system SHALL optionally approve pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Approve action_required runs\n92: - **GIVEN** `pull_request_target` on `main` or `release-**` with label/sync events\n93: - **WHEN** the contributor is not first-time (more than one PR) or PR has `ok-to-test`\n94: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL list workflow runs for the head SHA with `status: action_required` and call `approveWorkflowRun` for each\n\n(End of file - total 94 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# CI/CD Specification\n\n## Purpose\nAutomate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Pull request build verification\nThe system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the “Agentcube CI Workflow” job runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n\n### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\nThe system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n\n#### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/ci-cd/spec.md","time":{"start":1775878959295,"end":1775878959302}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775878959328,"sessionID":"ses_28560f931ffe4C5vIqrKBCG3xA","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa270c90015Fgk3Q6QKMFEDO","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7aa2485d001r1PgvI7qspPGg2","sessionID":"ses_28560f931ffe4C5vIqrKBCG3xA","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":20901,"input":20497,"output":369,"reasoning":35,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.006324176}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775878963292,"sessionID":"ses_28560f931ffe4C5vIqrKBCG3xA","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa280590010mao8qp92Fifj3","messageID":"msg_d7aa270f6001wB3R2rvSwtMH9F","sessionID":"ses_28560f931ffe4C5vIqrKBCG3xA","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878965316,"sessionID":"ses_28560f931ffe4C5vIqrKBCG3xA","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa2844f001D2LzHpdhN4XCez","messageID":"msg_d7aa270f6001wB3R2rvSwtMH9F","sessionID":"ses_28560f931ffe4C5vIqrKBCG3xA","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_137be40d308e480584a8e054","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: This AR covers the HTTP底层客户端 (HTTP underlying client layer) for the AgentCube Python SDK. It provides:\n8: \n9: 1. **Control Plane Client** — HTTP client for Workload Manager session lifecycle (create/delete sessions).\n10: 2. **Code Interpreter Data Plane Client** — HTTP client for Router-based code execution and file operations.\n11: 3. **Agent Runtime Data Plane Client** — HTTP client for Router-based agent invocation.\n12: 4. **HTTP Utilities** — Session factory, token reader, logger factory.\n13: 5. **Exception Hierarchy** — Structured error types for SDK operations.\n14: \n15: ### 1.2 System Context\n16: \n17: ```\n18: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n19: │                         User Application                            │\n20: │  ┌───────────────────────────┐   ┌─────────────────────────────┐   │\n21: │  │   CodeInterpreterClient   │   │    AgentRuntimeClient       │   │\n22: │  │   (High-level facade)     │   │    (High-level facade)      │   │\n23: │  └───────────┬───────────────┘   └──────────────┬──────────────┘   │\n24: │              │                                   │                   │\n25: │  ┌───────────▼───────────────┐   ┌──────────────▼──────────────┐   │\n26: │  │   ControlPlaneClient      │   │   CodeInterpreterDataPlane  │   │\n27: │  │   (Workload Manager)      │   │   AgentRuntimeDataPlane     │   │\n28: │  └───────────┬───────────────┘   └──────────────┬──────────────┘   │\n29: └──────────────┼──────────────────────────────────┼──────────────────┘\n30:                │                                  │\n31:                ▼                                  ▼\n32:     ┌──────────────────────┐          ┌────────────────────────┐\n33:     │  Workload Manager    │          │  Router (Data Plane)   │\n34:     │  (Control Plane API) │          │  /v1/namespaces/...    │\n35:     └──────────────────────┘          └────────────────────────┘\n36: ```\n37: \n38: ### 1.3 Design Principles\n39: \n40: - **No single `Configuration` class**: Defaults and environment resolution are distributed across client constructors.\n41: - **Context manager support**: All clients support `with` statement for proper resource cleanup.\n42: - **Session header convention**: Lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` for all Router requests.\n43: - **Timeout safety**: Read timeout buffer (`+2.0s`) for command execution to avoid premature `ReadTimeout`.\n44: - **Connection pooling**: `HTTPAdapter` with configurable pool size for all HTTP sessions.\n45: \n46: ### 1.4 Package Structure\n47: \n48: ```\n49: sdk-python/\n50: ├── pyproject.toml                          # Package metadata, dependencies\n51: ├── agentcube/\n52: │   ├── __init__.py                         # Public exports: CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient\n53: │   ├── code_interpreter.py                 # CodeInterpreterClient (high-level facade)\n54: │   ├── agent_runtime.py                    # AgentRuntimeClient (high-level facade)\n55: │   ├── exceptions.py                       # Exception hierarchy\n56: │   ├── clients/\n57: │   │   ├── __init__.py                     # Re-exports: ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient, AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n58: │   │   ├── control_plane.py                # ControlPlaneClient (Workload Manager HTTP)\n59: │   │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py  # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient (Router HTTP)\n60: │   │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py     # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (Router HTTP)\n61: │   └── utils/\n62: │       ├── __init__.py                     # Empty module marker\n63: │       ├── http.py                         # create_session()\n64: │       ├── utils.py                        # read_token_from_file()\n65: │       └── log.py                          # get_logger()\n66: ├── examples/\n67: │   ├── basic_usage.py\n68: │   └── agent_runtime_usage.py\n69: ├── scripts/\n70: │   └── e2e_picod_test.py\n71: └── tests/\n72:     ├── test_code_interpreter.py\n73:     ├── test_agent_runtime.py\n74:     ├── test_control_plane.py\n75:     ├── test_data_plane.py\n76:     └── test_exceptions.py\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ### 1.5 Dependencies\n80: \n81: ```toml\n82: dependencies = [\n83:     \"requests\",\n84:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n85:     \"cryptography\",\n86: ]\n87: \n88: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n89: \n90: [build-system]\n91: requires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\n92: build-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n93: \n94: [tool.setuptools.packages.find]\n95: where = [\".\"]\n96: include = [\"agentcube*\"]\n97: namespaces = false\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## 2. Data Structures\n103: \n104: ### 2.1 Exception Hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n105: \n106: ```\n107: Exception\n108: └── AgentCubeError (base for all SDK exceptions)\n109:     ├── CommandExecutionError (non-zero exit code from remote command)\n110:     │   Attributes: exit_code, stderr, command\n111:     │   Message: \"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\"\n112:     ├── SessionError (session creation/management failures)\n113:     └── DataPlaneError (data plane operation failures)\n114: ```\n115: \n116: **Design Notes:**\n117: - `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` are defined for extension but not raised by core client modules.\n118: - Core clients raise `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`.\n119: \n120: ### 2.2 Client Instance State\n121: \n122: #### `CodeInterpreterClient`\n123: | Field | Type | Source |\n124: |-------|------|--------|\n125: | `name` | `str` | Constructor arg (default: `\"my-interpreter\"`) |\n126: | `namespace` | `str` | Constructor arg (default: `\"default\"`) |\n127: | `ttl` | `int` | Constructor arg (default: `3600`) |\n128: | `verbose` | `bool` | Constructor arg (default: `False`) |\n129: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | `get_logger()` |\n130: | `cp_client` | `ControlPlaneClient` | Created in `__init__` |\n131: | `router_url` | `str` | Arg or `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n132: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Arg or from `create_session()` |\n133: | `dp_client` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Created in `_init_data_plane()` |\n134: \n135: #### `AgentRuntimeClient`\n136: | Field | Type | Source |\n137: |-------|------|--------|\n138: | `agent_name` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n139: | `namespace` | `str` | Constructor arg (default: `\"default\"`) |\n140: | `timeout` | `int` | Constructor arg (default: `120`) |\n141: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Constructor arg (default: `5.0`) |\n142: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | `get_logger()` |\n143: | `router_url` | `str` | Arg or `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n144: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | From `bootstrap_session_id()` |\n145: | `dp_client` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Created in `__init__` |\n146: \n147: #### `ControlPlaneClient`\n148: | Field | Type | Source |\n149: |-------|------|--------|\n150: | `base_url` | `str` | Arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env |\n151: | `auth_token` | `str` | Arg or SA token file |\n152: | `timeout` | `int` | Default: `120` |\n153: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Default: `5.0` |\n154: | `pool_connections` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n155: | `pool_maxsize` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n156: | `session` | `requests.Session` | Created via `create_session()` |\n157: \n158: #### `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n159: | Field | Type | Source |\n160: |-------|------|--------|\n161: | `session_id` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n162: | `base_url` | `str` | Explicit arg or `urljoin(router_url, base_path)` |\n163: | `timeout` | `int` | Default: `120` |\n164: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Default: `5.0` |\n165: | `pool_connections` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n166: | `pool_maxsize` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n167: | `session` | `requests.Session` | Created via `create_session()` |\n168: \n169: #### `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n170: | Field | Type | Source |\n171: |-------|------|--------|\n172: | `SESSION_HEADER` | `str` | Class constant: `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"` |\n173: | `router_url` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n174: | `namespace` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n175: | `agent_name` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n176: | `base_url` | `str` | `urljoin(router_url, base_path)` |\n177: | `timeout` | `int` | Default: `120` |\n178: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Default: `5.0` |\n179: | `pool_connections` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n180: | `pool_maxsize` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n181: | `session` | `requests.Session` | Created via `create_session()` |\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## 3. API Contracts\n186: \n187: ### 3.1 HTTP Utilities\n188: \n189: #### `create_session` (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n190: \n191: ```python\n192: def create_session(\n193:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n194:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n195: ) -> requests.Session:\n196:     \"\"\"Create a requests.Session with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling.\"\"\"\n197: ```\n198: \n199: - Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://`\n200: - Default pool: 10 connections, max size 10\n201: \n202: #### `read_token_from_file` (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n203: \n204: ```python\n205: def read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str:\n206:     \"\"\"Read and strip token from file. Returns '' on FileNotFoundError.\"\"\"\n207: ```\n208: \n209: #### `get_logger` (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n210: \n211: ```python\n212: def get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger:\n213:     \"\"\"Create a configured logger.\"\"\"\n214: ```\n215: \n216: ### 3.2 Control Plane Client (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n217: \n218: #### Constructor Resolution\n219: \n220: | Setting | Primary | Fallback |\n221: |---------|---------|----------|\n222: | `base_url` | `workload_manager_url` arg | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env |\n223: | `auth_token` | `auth_token` arg | `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` |\n224: \n225: #### HTTP Endpoints\n226: \n227: | Method | Path | Body | Response | Notes |\n228: |--------|------|------|----------|-------|\n229: | `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | `{\"name\", \"namespace\", \"ttl\", \"metadata\"}` | `{\"data\": {\"sessionId\": \"...\"}}` | Returns `sessionId` |\n230: | `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | — | 2xx success, 404 = success | 404 treated as success |\n231: \n232: #### Methods\n233: \n234: ```python\n235: class ControlPlaneClient:\n236:     def __init__(\n237:         self,\n238:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n239:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n240:         timeout: int = 120,\n241:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n242:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n243:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n244:     )\n245: \n246:     def create_session(\n247:         self,\n248:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n249:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n250:         metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n251:         ttl: int = 3600,\n252:     ) -> str:\n253:         \"\"\"Create session, return session_id. Raise ValueError if sessionId absent.\"\"\"\n254: \n255:     def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool:\n256:         \"\"\"Delete session. Return True on success or 404, False on other failures.\"\"\"\n257: \n258:     def close(self) -> None:\n259:         \"\"\"Close the underlying requests.Session.\"\"\"\n260: ```\n261: \n262: **Headers:**\n263: - `Content-Type: application/json`\n264: - `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token non-empty)\n265: \n266: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` tuple on each request\n267: \n268: ### 3.3 Code Interpreter Data Plane Client (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n269: \n270: #### Base URL Construction\n271: \n272: ```python\n273: if base_url is None:\n274:     base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n275:     self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n276: ```\n277: \n278: #### HTTP Endpoints (relative to `self.base_url`)\n279: \n280: | Method | Path | Body | Notes |\n281: |--------|------|------|-------|\n282: | `POST` | `api/execute` | `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` | Read timeout = `timeout_value + 2.0` |\n283: | `POST` | `api/files` | `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` | JSON body |\n284: | `POST` | `api/files` | multipart `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` | Upload |\n285: | `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | — | `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`, `stream=True` |\n286: | `GET` | `api/files` | query `path` | List files |\n287: \n288: #### Methods\n289: \n290: ```python\n291: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n292:     def __init__(\n293:         self,\n294:         session_id: str,\n295:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n296:         namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n297:         cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n298:         base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n299:         timeout: int = 120,\n300:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n301:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n302:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n303:     )\n304: \n305:     def _request(\n306:         self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs\n307:     ) -> requests.Response:\n308:         \"\"\"Internal HTTP request helper. Sets Content-Type: application/json when body is set.\"\"\"\n309: \n310:     def execute_command(\n311:         self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None\n312:     ) -> str:\n313:         \"\"\"Execute command. Raise CommandExecutionError on non-zero exit.\"\"\"\n314: \n315:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str:\n316:         \"\"\"Execute code. Python variants write timestamped .py file first.\"\"\"\n317: \n318:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n319:         \"\"\"Write file content (base64 encoded).\"\"\"\n320: \n321:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n322:         \"\"\"Upload file via multipart form.\"\"\"\n323: \n324:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None:\n325:         \"\"\"Download file with streaming.\"\"\"\n326: \n327:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any:\n328:         \"\"\"List files at path.\"\"\"\n329: \n330:     def close(self) -> None:\n331:         \"\"\"Close the underlying requests.Session.\"\"\"\n332: ```\n333: \n334: **Headers:**\n335: - Default session: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n336: - JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json` (when `body` is set in `_request`)\n337: - Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only (no JSON Content-Type)\n338: \n339: **Note:** Router handles JWT; SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane.\n340: \n341: #### `execute_command` Timeout Logic\n342: \n343: ```python\n344: effective_timeout = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\n345: # PicoD timeout string\n346: timeout_str = f\"{int(effective_timeout)}s\"\n347: # Read timeout buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout\n348: read_timeout = effective_timeout + 2.0\n349: request_timeout = (self.connect_timeout, read_timeout)\n350: ```\n351: \n352: #### `run_code` Python Execution Path\n353: \n354: - Languages: `python`, `py`, `python3`\n355: - Writes timestamped `.py` file via `write_file`\n356: - Executes `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n357: \n358: ### 3.4 Agent Runtime Data Plane Client (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n359: \n360: #### Base URL Construction\n361: \n362: ```python\n363: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n364: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n365: ```\n366: \n367: #### HTTP Endpoints\n368: \n369: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n370: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n371: | `GET` | `self.base_url` | Session default headers only | — |\n372: | `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n373: \n374: #### Methods\n375: \n376: ```python\n377: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n378:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n379: \n380:     def __init__(\n381:         self,\n382:         router_url: str,\n383:         namespace: str,\n384:         agent_name: str,\n385:         timeout: int = 120,\n386:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n387:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n388:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n389:     )\n390: \n391:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str:\n392:         \"\"\"GET base_url, read x-agentcube-session-id header. Raise ValueError if missing.\"\"\"\n393: \n394:     def invoke(\n395:         self,\n396:         session_id: str,\n397:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n398:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n399:     ) -> requests.Response:\n400:         \"\"\"POST JSON payload with session header.\"\"\"\n401: \n402:     def close(self) -> None:\n403:         \"\"\"Close the underlying requests.Session.\"\"\"\n404: ```\n405: \n406: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` defaults to `self.timeout` (120)\n407: \n408: ### 3.5 High-Level Facades\n409: \n410: #### `CodeInterpreterClient` (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`)\n411: \n412: ```python\n413: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n414:     def __init__(\n415:         self,\n416:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n417:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n418:         ttl: int = 3600,\n419:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n420:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n421:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n422:         verbose: bool = False,\n423:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n424:     )\n425: \n426:     def _init_data_plane(self) -> None\n427:     def __enter__(self) -> \"CodeInterpreterClient\"\n428:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None\n429:     def stop(self) -> None\n430:     def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n431:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n432:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n433:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n434:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None\n435:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any\n436: ```\n437: \n438: **Lifecycle:**\n439: 1. If `session_id` provided: reuse it, skip control plane\n440: 2. If `session_id` not provided: call `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()`, then `_init_data_plane()`\n441: 3. On `_init_data_plane()` failure: log warning, `delete_session()`, set `session_id=None`, re-raise\n442: \n443: #### `AgentRuntimeClient` (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`)\n444: \n445: ```python\n446: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n447:     def __init__(\n448:         self,\n449:         agent_name: str,\n450:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n451:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n452:         verbose: bool = False,\n453:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n454:         timeout: int = 120,\n455:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n456:     )\n457: \n458:     def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\"\n459:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None\n460:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any\n461:     def close(self) -> None\n462: ```\n463: \n464: **Lifecycle:**\n465: 1. If `session_id` not provided: call `dp_client.bootstrap_session_id()`\n466: 2. `invoke()` requires `session_id` to be set, else `ValueError`\n467: \n468: ### 3.6 Public Package Surface\n469: \n470: ```python\n471: # agentcube/__init__.py\n472: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n473: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n474: \n475: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n476: ```\n477: \n478: ```python\n479: # agentcube/clients/__init__.py\n480: __all__ = [\n481:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n482:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n483:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n484: ]\n485: ```\n486: \n487: **Note:** Only `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` are exported from the root package. Data plane and control plane clients are internal implementation details accessible via `agentcube.clients.*`.\n488: \n489: ---\n490: \n491: ## 4. Configuration Summary\n492: \n493: | Component | Resolved Settings |\n494: |-----------|-------------------|\n495: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ← `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ← `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n496: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient`; `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `session_id` |\n497: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n498: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` passed to data plane |\n499: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | same timeout defaults as above |\n500: \n501: ---\n502: \n503: ## 5. Error Handling\n504: \n505: ### 5.1 Error Classification\n506: \n507: | Scenario | Exception | Source |\n508: |----------|-----------|--------|\n509: | Router URL missing | `ValueError` | `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` |\n510: | Session ID bootstrap missing header | `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id()` |\n511: | Invoke without session | `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")` | `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke()` |\n512: | Command non-zero exit | `CommandExecutionError(exit_code, stderr, command)` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.execute_command()` |\n513: | Create session missing sessionId | `ValueError` | `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` |\n514: | Delete session 404 | Returns `True` (not exception) | `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()` |\n515: | Delete session other failure | Logs, returns `False` | `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()` |\n516: | Data plane init failure | Logs warning, cleanup, re-raise | `CodeInterpreterClient._init_data_plane()` |\n517: | HTTP errors | `requests.HTTPError` or similar | `requests` library |\n518: \n519: ### 5.2 Timeout Strategy\n520: \n521: | Component | Connect Timeout | Read Timeout | Notes |\n522: |-----------|-----------------|--------------|-------|\n523: | Control Plane | `5.0s` | `120s` | Default, overridable per call |\n524: | Code Interpreter Data Plane | `5.0s` | `120s` | Default, overridable per call |\n525: | `execute_command` | `5.0s` | `timeout_value + 2.0s` | Buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout |\n526: | Agent Runtime Data Plane | `5.0s` | `120s` | Default, overridable per call |\n527: \n528: **Timeout tuple format:** `(connect_timeout, read_timeout)` passed to `requests`\n529: \n530: ### 5.3 Exception Flow\n531: \n532: ```\n533: ValueError                    ← Configuration errors, missing session, missing headers\n534: CommandExecutionError         ← Non-zero exit code from remote command\n535: requests.RequestException     ← HTTP failures (connection errors, timeouts)\n536: requests.HTTPError            ← Non-2xx responses (if raised)\n537: ```\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## 6. Implementation Notes\n542: \n543: ### 6.1 Session Header Consistency\n544: \n545: All Router requests use lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id`:\n546: \n547: - `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`: Set as default session header in `__init__`\n548: - `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`: Class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`, set explicitly on each `POST` request\n549: - Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` set explicitly on the request (no JSON Content-Type)\n550: \n551: ### 6.2 Timeout Tuple Logic\n552: \n553: For `execute_command`:\n554: \n555: ```python\n556: effective_timeout = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\n557: timeout_str = f\"{int(effective_timeout)}s\"  # PicoD timeout string\n558: read_timeout = effective_timeout + 2.0      # Buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout\n559: request_timeout = (self.connect_timeout, read_timeout)\n560: ```\n561: \n562: For `invoke`:\n563: \n564: ```python\n565: effective_timeout = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\n566: request_timeout = (self.connect_timeout, effective_timeout)\n567: ```\n568: \n569: ### 6.3 Context Manager Pattern\n570: \n571: ```python\n572: # Code Interpreter\n573: with CodeInterpreterClient(\n574:     name=\"my-interpreter\",\n575:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n576: ) as client:\n577:     result = client.execute_command(\"echo hello\")\n578: \n579: # Agent Runtime\n580: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n581:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n582:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n583: ) as client:\n584:     response = client.invoke({\"action\": \"query\"})\n585: ```\n586: \n587: ### 6.4 Data Plane Init Failure Cleanup\n588: \n589: ```python\n590: def _init_data_plane(self) -> None:\n591:     try:\n592:         self.dp_client = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(\n593:             session_id=self.session_id,\n594:             router_url=self.router_url,\n595:             namespace=self.namespace,\n596:             cr_name=self.name,\n597:         )\n598:     except Exception:\n599:         self.logger.warning(\"Data plane init failed, cleaning up session %s\", self.session_id)\n600:         self.cp_client.delete_session(self.session_id)\n601:         self.session_id = None\n602:         raise\n603: ```\n604: \n605: ---\n606: \n607: ## 7. Testing Strategy\n608: \n609: ### 7.1 Test Categories\n610: \n611: | Category | Scope | Tools |\n612: |----------|-------|-------|\n613: | Unit tests | Individual client methods, exception handling | `pytest`, `unittest.mock` |\n614: | Integration tests | HTTP endpoint contracts (mocked server) | `pytest`, `responses` or `httpretty` |\n615: | E2E tests | Full lifecycle against PicoD | `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` |\n616: \n617: ### 7.2 Key Test Scenarios\n618: \n619: #### `CodeInterpreterClient`\n620: \n621: | Test Name | Description |\n622: |-----------|-------------|\n623: | `test_context_manager_cleanup` | Context manager cleanup calls `stop()` |\n624: | `test_data_plane_init_failure_cleanup` | Data plane init failure cleans up session and re-raises |\n625: | `test_router_url_required` | Router URL required (arg or env) |\n626: | `test_execute_command_nonzero_exit` | `execute_command` raises `CommandExecutionError` on non-zero exit |\n627: | `test_run_code_python_writes_file` | `run_code` with Python writes timestamped file and executes |\n628: | `test_reuse_session_id_skips_control_plane` | Reuse of provided `session_id` skips control plane |\n629: \n630: #### `AgentRuntimeClient`\n631: \n632: | Test Name | Description |\n633: |-----------|-------------|\n634: | `test_context_manager_cleanup` | Context manager cleanup calls `close()` |\n635: | `test_bootstrap_session_id` | Bootstrap session ID reads header, raises `ValueError` if missing |\n636: | `test_invoke_without_session` | Invoke without session raises `ValueError` |\n637: | `test_invoke_timeout_tuple` | Invoke timeout tuple construction |\n638: \n639: #### `ControlPlaneClient`\n640: \n641: | Test Name | Description |\n642: |-----------|-------------|\n643: | `test_create_session_returns_session_id` | Create session returns `sessionId`, raises `ValueError` if absent |\n644: | `test_delete_session_404_returns_true` | Delete session 404 returns `True` |\n645: | `test_delete_session_failure_returns_false` | Delete session other failure returns `False` |\n646: | `test_auth_token_from_sa_file` | Auth token from SA file fallback |\n647: | `test_base_url_from_env` | Base URL from env fallback |\n648: \n649: #### `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n650: \n651: | Test Name | Description |\n652: |-----------|-------------|\n653: | `test_execute_command_timeout_buffer` | Execute command timeout buffer (`+2.0s`) |\n654: | `test_write_file_base64` | Write file base64 encoding |\n655: | `test_upload_file_multipart_session_header` | Upload file multipart with session header |\n656: | `test_download_file_streaming` | Download file streaming |\n657: | `test_list_files_query_parameter` | List files query parameter |\n658: \n659: #### `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n660: \n661: | Test Name | Description |\n662: |-----------|-------------|\n663: | `test_bootstrap_session_id` | Bootstrap session ID from GET response header |\n664: | `test_bootstrap_missing_header_raises` | Bootstrap missing header raises `ValueError` |\n665: | `test_invoke_with_session_header` | Invoke POST with session header and JSON body |\n666: \n667: #### Exceptions\n668: \n669: | Test Name | Description |\n670: |-----------|-------------|\n671: | `test_command_execution_error_attributes` | `CommandExecutionError` attributes and message format |\n672: | `test_exception_hierarchy` | Exception hierarchy (`AgentCubeError` base) |\n673: | `test_session_error_data_plane_error_defined` | `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` defined but not raised by core |\n674: \n675: ### 7.3 Mocking Strategy\n676: \n677: - Mock `requests.Session` and its methods (`get`, `post`, `delete`)\n678: - Mock `read_token_from_file` for auth token tests\n679: - Mock environment variables with `monkeypatch`\n680: - Use `responses` library for HTTP endpoint contract tests\n681: \n682: ### 7.4 Example Test Structure\n683: \n684: ```python\n685: # tests/test_code_interpreter.py\n686: class TestCodeInterpreterClient:\n687:     def test_context_manager_cleanup(self, mock_cp_client, mock_dp_client): ...\n688:     def test_data_plane_init_failure_cleanup(self, mock_cp_client): ...\n689:     def test_router_url_required(self): ...\n690:     def test_execute_command_nonzero_exit(self, mock_dp_client): ...\n691:     def test_run_code_python_writes_file(self, mock_dp_client): ...\n692:     def test_reuse_session_id_skips_control_plane(self): ...\n693: \n694: # tests/test_control_plane.py\n695: class TestControlPlaneClient:\n696:     def test_create_session_returns_session_id(self, mock_session): ...\n697:     def test_create_session_missing_session_id_raises(self, mock_session): ...\n698:     def test_delete_session_404_returns_true(self, mock_session): ...\n699:     def test_delete_session_failure_returns_false(self, mock_session): ...\n700:     def test_auth_token_from_sa_file(self, mock_read_token): ...\n701:     def test_base_url_from_env(self, monkeypatch): ...\n702: \n703: # tests/test_data_plane.py\n704: class TestCodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n705:     def test_execute_command_timeout_buffer(self, mock_session): ...\n706:     def test_write_file_base64(self, mock_session): ...\n707:     def test_upload_file_multipart_session_header(self, mock_session): ...\n708: \n709: class TestAgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n710:     def test_bootstrap_session_id(self, mock_session): ...\n711:     def test_bootstrap_missing_header_raises(self, mock_session): ...\n712:     def test_invoke_with_session_header(self, mock_session): ...\n713: ```\n714: \n715: ---\n716: \n717: ## 8. Usage Examples\n718: \n719: ### 8.1 Code Interpreter — Basic Usage\n720: \n721: ```python\n722: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n723: \n724: with CodeInterpreterClient(\n725:     name=\"my-interpreter\",\n726:     namespace=\"default\",\n727:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n728: ) as client:\n729:     # Execute shell command\n730:     result = client.execute_command(\"echo hello\")\n731:     print(result)\n732: \n733:     # Run Python code\n734:     result = client.run_code(\"python\", \"print('Hello, World!')\")\n735:     print(result)\n736: \n737:     # Write file\n738:     client.write_file(\"content\", \"/tmp/test.txt\")\n739: \n740:     # List files\n741:     files = client.list_files(\"/tmp\")\n742:     print(files)\n743: ```\n744: \n745: ### 8.2 Code Interpreter — Reuse Session\n746: \n747: ```python\n748: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n749: \n750: client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n751:     session_id=\"existing-session-id\",\n752:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n753: )\n754: \n755: try:\n756:     result = client.execute_command(\"ls -la\")\n757: finally:\n758:     client.stop()\n759: ```\n760: \n761: ### 8.3 Agent Runtime — Basic Usage\n762: \n763: ```python\n764: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n765: \n766: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n767:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n768:     namespace=\"production\",\n769:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n770: ) as client:\n771:     response = client.invoke({\n772:         \"action\": \"process\",\n773:         \"data\": {\"input\": \"hello world\"}\n774:     })\n775:     print(response)\n776: ```\n777: \n778: ### 8.4 Agent Runtime — Custom Timeout\n779: \n780: ```python\n781: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n782: \n783: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n784:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n785:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n786:     timeout=300,  # 5 minute read timeout\n787: ) as client:\n788:     response = client.invoke(\n789:         {\"action\": \"long_running_task\"},\n790:         timeout=600  # Override to 10 minutes for this call\n791:     )\n792: ```\n\n(End of file - total 792 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis AR covers the HTTP底层客户端 (HTTP underlying client layer) for the AgentCube Python SDK. It provides:\n\n1. **Control Plane Client** — HTTP client for Workload Manager session lifecycle (create/delete sessions).\n2. **Code Interpreter Data Plane Client** — HTTP client for Router-based code execution and file operations.\n3. **Agent Runtime Data Plane Client** — HTTP client for Router-based agent invocation.\n4. **HTTP Utilities** — Session factory, token reader, logger factory.\n5. **Exception Hierarchy** — Structured error types for SDK operations.\n\n### 1.2 System Context\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         User Application                            │\n│  ┌───────────────────────────┐   ┌─────────────────────────────┐   │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775878965307,"end":1775878965313}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878966551,"sessionID":"ses_28560f931ffe4C5vIqrKBCG3xA","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa28910001MEYbf14w7y9tbE","messageID":"msg_d7aa270f6001wB3R2rvSwtMH9F","sessionID":"ses_28560f931ffe4C5vIqrKBCG3xA","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_4cdc084ccdc24057bce8babd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/Makefile"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/Makefile</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — Makefile 构建目标体系\n2: # AR-033: Unified build, test, docker, lint, helm, and python targets\n3: \n4: # ==============================================================================\n5: # Variables and Configuration\n6: # ==============================================================================\n7: \n8: TAG        ?= latest\n9: REGISTRY   ?= agentcube\n10: GOOS       ?= $(shell go env GOOS)\n11: GOARCH     ?= $(shell go env GOARCH)\n12: BIN_DIR    ?= bin\n13: LDFLAGS    ?= -s -w\n14: VERBOSE    ?=\n15: \n16: # Go binaries\n17: GO_BINARIES := router workloadmanager agentd picod\n18: \n19: # Docker images (name -> Dockerfile mapping)\n20: DOCKER_AGENTCUBE_DOCKERFILE := docker/Dockerfile\n21: DOCKER_ROUTER_DOCKERFILE    := docker/Dockerfile.router\n22: DOCKER_PICOD_DOCKERFILE     := docker/Dockerfile.picod\n23: DOCKER_IMAGES               := agentcube router picod\n24: \n25: # Helm chart path\n26: HELM_CHART_DIR := manifests/charts/base\n27: \n28: # Python paths\n29: PYTHON_SDK_DIR  := python-sdk\n30: PYTHON_CLI_DIR  := cmd/cli\n31: \n32: # ==============================================================================\n33: # Verbosity helper\n34: # ==============================================================================\n35: \n36: ifeq ($(VERBOSE),1)\n37:   V =\n38:   Q =\n39: else\n40:   V = @\n41:   Q = @\n42: endif\n43: \n44: # ==============================================================================\n45: # .PHONY declarations\n46: # ==============================================================================\n47: \n48: .PHONY: all build clean test test-coverage test-chart lint fmt vet \\\n49:         docker helm-lint helm-template python-lint python-test ci \\\n50:         build/router build/workloadmanager build/agentd build/picod \\\n51:         docker/agentcube docker/router docker/picod\n52: \n53: # ==============================================================================\n54: # Composite Targets\n55: # ==============================================================================\n56: \n57: all: build test lint\n58: \n59: ci: build test test-coverage lint helm-lint\n60: \n61: # ==============================================================================\n62: # Go Build Targets\n63: # ==============================================================================\n64: \n65: build: build/router build/workloadmanager build/agentd build/picod\n66: \n67: build/router:\n68: \t$(Q)mkdir -p $(BIN_DIR)\n69: \t$(Q)echo \"  BUILD   router ($(GOOS)/$(GOARCH))\"\n70: \t$(V)GOOS=$(GOOS) GOARCH=$(GOARCH) go build -ldflags '$(LDFLAGS)' -o $(BIN_DIR)/router ./cmd/router\n71: \n72: build/workloadmanager:\n73: \t$(Q)mkdir -p $(BIN_DIR)\n74: \t$(Q)echo \"  BUILD   workloadmanager ($(GOOS)/$(GOARCH))\"\n75: \t$(V)GOOS=$(GOOS) GOARCH=$(GOARCH) go build -ldflags '$(LDFLAGS)' -o $(BIN_DIR)/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager\n76: \n77: build/agentd:\n78: \t$(Q)mkdir -p $(BIN_DIR)\n79: \t$(Q)echo \"  BUILD   agentd ($(GOOS)/$(GOARCH))\"\n80: \t$(V)GOOS=$(GOOS) GOARCH=$(GOARCH) go build -ldflags '$(LDFLAGS)' -o $(BIN_DIR)/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n81: \n82: build/picod:\n83: \t$(Q)mkdir -p $(BIN_DIR)\n84: \t$(Q)echo \"  BUILD   picod ($(GOOS)/$(GOARCH))\"\n85: \t$(V)GOOS=$(GOOS) GOARCH=$(GOARCH) go build -ldflags '$(LDFLAGS)' -o $(BIN_DIR)/picod ./cmd/picod\n86: \n87: clean:\n88: \t$(Q)rm -rf $(BIN_DIR)\n89: \t$(Q)echo \"  CLEAN   build artifacts removed\"\n90: \n91: # ==============================================================================\n92: # Docker Build Targets\n93: # ==============================================================================\n94: \n95: docker: $(addprefix docker/,$(DOCKER_IMAGES))\n96: \n97: docker/agentcube:\n98: \t$(Q)echo \"  DOCKER  $(REGISTRY)/agentcube:$(TAG)\"\n99: \t$(V)docker build -t $(REGISTRY)/agentcube:$(TAG) -f $(DOCKER_AGENTCUBE_DOCKERFILE) .\n100: \n101: docker/router:\n102: \t$(Q)echo \"  DOCKER  $(REGISTRY)/router:$(TAG)\"\n103: \t$(V)docker build -t $(REGISTRY)/router:$(TAG) -f $(DOCKER_ROUTER_DOCKERFILE) .\n104: \n105: docker/picod:\n106: \t$(Q)echo \"  DOCKER  $(REGISTRY)/picod:$(TAG)\"\n107: \t$(V)docker build -t $(REGISTRY)/picod:$(TAG) -f $(DOCKER_PICOD_DOCKERFILE) .\n108: \n109: # ==============================================================================\n110: # Test Targets\n111: # ==============================================================================\n112: \n113: test:\n114: \t$(Q)echo \"  TEST    go test ./...\"\n115: \t$(V)go test ./...\n116: \n117: test-coverage:\n118: \t$(Q)echo \"  COVER   go test -coverprofile=coverage.out ./...\"\n119: \t$(V)go test -coverprofile=coverage.out ./...\n120: \n121: test-chart:\n122: \t$(Q)echo \"  TEST    helm chart render\"\n123: \t$(V)bash test/chart/test_render.sh\n124: \n125: # ==============================================================================\n126: # Code Quality Targets\n127: # ==============================================================================\n128: \n129: lint:\n130: \t$(Q)if ! command -v golangci-lint >/dev/null 2>&1; then \\\n131: \t\techo \"ERROR: golangci-lint is required but not installed.\"; \\\n132: \t\texit 1; \\\n133: \tfi\n134: \t$(Q)echo \"  LINT    golangci-lint run\"\n135: \t$(V)golangci-lint run\n136: \n137: fmt:\n138: \t$(Q)echo \"  FMT     go fmt ./...\"\n139: \t$(V)go fmt ./...\n140: \n141: vet:\n142: \t$(Q)echo \"  VET     go vet ./...\"\n143: \t$(V)go vet ./...\n144: \n145: # ==============================================================================\n146: # Helm Targets\n147: # ==============================================================================\n148: \n149: helm-lint:\n150: \t$(Q)if ! command -v helm >/dev/null 2>&1; then \\\n151: \t\techo \"ERROR: helm is required but not installed.\"; \\\n152: \t\texit 1; \\\n153: \tfi\n154: \t$(Q)echo \"  HELM    lint $(HELM_CHART_DIR)\"\n155: \t$(V)helm lint $(HELM_CHART_DIR)\n156: \n157: helm-template:\n158: \t$(Q)if ! command -v helm >/dev/null 2>&1; then \\\n159: \t\techo \"ERROR: helm is required but not installed.\"; \\\n160: \t\texit 1; \\\n161: \tfi\n162: \t$(Q)echo \"  HELM    template $(HELM_CHART_DIR)\"\n163: \t$(V)helm template release $(HELM_CHART_DIR)\n164: \n165: # ==============================================================================\n166: # Python Targets\n167: # ==============================================================================\n168: \n169: python-lint:\n170: \t$(Q)if command -v ruff >/dev/null 2>&1; then \\\n171: \t\techo \"  PYLINT  ruff check $(PYTHON_SDK_DIR) $(PYTHON_CLI_DIR)\"; \\\n172: \t\truff check $(PYTHON_SDK_DIR) $(PYTHON_CLI_DIR); \\\n173: \telif command -v flake8 >/dev/null 2>&1; then \\\n174: \t\techo \"  PYLINT  flake8 $(PYTHON_SDK_DIR) $(PYTHON_CLI_DIR)\"; \\\n175: \t\tflake8 $(PYTHON_SDK_DIR) $(PYTHON_CLI_DIR); \\\n176: \telse \\\n177: \t\techo \"WARNING: No Python lint tool found (ruff or flake8). Install one to enable linting.\"; \\\n178: \tfi\n179: \n180: python-test:\n181: \t$(Q)if command -v pytest >/dev/null 2>&1; then \\\n182: \t\techo \"  PYTEST  pytest $(PYTHON_SDK_DIR)/tests $(PYTHON_CLI_DIR)/tests\"; \\\n183: \t\tpytest $(PYTHON_SDK_DIR)/tests $(PYTHON_CLI_DIR)/tests; \\\n184: \telse \\\n185: \t\techo \"WARNING: pytest is not installed. Install it to run Python tests.\"; \\\n186: \tfi\n\n(End of file - total 186 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — Makefile 构建目标体系\n# AR-033: Unified build, test, docker, lint, helm, and python targets\n\n# ==============================================================================\n# Variables and Configuration\n# ==============================================================================\n\nTAG        ?= latest\nREGISTRY   ?= agentcube\nGOOS       ?= $(shell go env GOOS)\nGOARCH     ?= $(shell go env GOARCH)\nBIN_DIR    ?= bin\nLDFLAGS    ?= -s -w\nVERBOSE    ?=\n\n# Go binaries\nGO_BINARIES := router workloadmanager agentd picod\n\n# Docker images (name -> Dockerfile mapping)\nDOCKER_AGENTCUBE_DOCKERFILE := docker/Dockerfile","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/Makefile","time":{"start":1775878966532,"end":1775878966549}}}}
